formThreeBId.notesToCertificate:
1.	It is the responsibility of management to prepare the financial statement of firm. The firm has prepared financial statement by following the mercantile method of accounting. The promoter has passed all necessary entries in accounts and reported all bank accounts in the financial statements and based on the unaudited accounts produced before us for given this certificate and relied on same for reporting to RERA Authority while certifying Form 3.
2.	Amount deposited and withdrawn from the bank account reflects only booking receipts collected and utilized in the project.
3.	Management of the entity has provided Customer ID, details of PAN / Aadhar Card, and Mobile Numbers of the allottees, Date of Registered Agreement for sale and Encumbrance Status and we have relied on the same while giving this certificate.
4.	We have checked the detail of Agreement for sale registered by the promoter and based on the certified detail from the promoter, we have given this certificate and fill the detail while giving this certificate. 
5.	The FSI Detail of the Project is as under
Total FSI of the Project is of Rs.3,32,30,106/- & Interest of Rs.24,94,989/-and hence total Amount mentioned while giving the certificate is of Rs. 3,57,25,095/- and out of which the promoter has paid of Rs.2,25,18,176/- 
6.	Total Estimated Statutory Cost is Rs.10,00,000/- of chakashni fee, development fee, Tree Planation and other fees payable to corporation and urban development authority.
